author: @econdoc3000
text: Hi Krish, your definition of quantiles is wrong! If you have 0.1=F(x) with F() being the cumulative density, then its 0.1 = F(x)=P(X<=x) NOT P(X<x). So the "1" in your example is the 10% quantile, because 10% of data is smaller OR EQUAL to 1. Equally, the 10 is the 100% quantile because 100% of the data is smaller or equal to 10.
